==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Douceur
<hw>Dou`ceur"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F., fr.
<ets>doux</ets> sweet. See <er>Douce</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Gentleness and sweetness of manner; agreeableness.</def>
<rj><au>Chesterfield.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A gift for service done or to be done; an
honorarium; a present; sometimes, a bribe.</def>
<rj><au>Burke.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Douche</ent>⟦br⟧
